snippet.title: Brittany Force makes the fastest run in NHRA history
snippet.description:
The first matchup of 340-plus-mph dragsters didn't disappoint as Brittany Force not only defeated Doug Kalitta but did it with the fastest speed ever, a national-record 341.85 mph on a 3.659 pass. Her run is quicker than her Funny Car teammate Austin Prock's 341.68 from last year's season finale. This event has now been host to four of the six fastest speeds in Top Fuel history. 


This is a @FendtTV record-setting performance.

nl-NL.title: Brittany Force maakt snelste run in de geschiedenis van de NHRA
nl-NL.description:
De eerste wedstrijd tussen dragsters met een snelheid van meer dan 550 km/u stelde niet teleur. Brittany Force versloeg niet alleen Doug Kalitta, maar deed dat ook met de hoogste snelheid ooit: een nationaal record van 550,8 km/u met een tijd van 3,659 mijl per uur. Haar run is sneller dan de 341,68 mijl per uur van haar Funny Car-teamgenoot Austin Prock uit de seizoensfinale van vorig jaar. Dit evenement heeft nu vier van de zes snelste snelheden in de geschiedenis van Top Fuel opgeleverd.

Dit is een recordprestatie van @FendtTV.

id.title: Brittany Force mencatatkan rekor lari tercepat dalam sejarah NHRA
id.description:
Pertarungan pertama dragster berkecepatan lebih dari 340 mph tidak mengecewakan karena Brittany Force tidak hanya mengalahkan Doug Kalitta, tetapi juga melakukannya dengan kecepatan tercepat yang pernah ada, rekor nasional 341,85 mph dengan waktu tempuh 3,659 detik. Acara ini kini telah menjadi tuan rumah bagi empat dari enam kecepatan tercepat dalam sejarah Top Fuel.

Ini adalah penampilan @FendtTV yang memecahkan rekor.

snippet.title: Pacquiao vs Barrios HIGHLIGHTS: July 19, 2025 | PBC PPV on Prime Video
snippet.description:
In the MGM Grand Garden Arena where Manny Pacquiao won his first title 2001, he returned to fight Mario Barrios for the WBC Welterweight World title in front of 14,000 cheering boxing fans. 

Pacquiao and Barrios went toe-to-toe for 12 hard fought rounds, fighting to a majority draw. Barrios retained his WBC belt and Manny Pacquiao showed the world that age is just a number. The legend can still fight.

id.title: Pola Cuaca Terburuk Musim Panas Akan Datang...
id.description:
Dalam prakiraan cuaca hari ini, kita membahas tentang perubahan pola cuaca BESAR yang akan membawa gelombang panas yang memecahkan rekor ke Amerika Serikat! Selain itu, badai besar akan membawa cuaca buruk, banjir besar, dan potensi badai tropis selama 7 hari ke depan. Ini termasuk potensi angin kencang, hujan es besar, dan ancaman tornado. Dapatkan semua detail terbaru dalam prakiraan cuaca hari ini.

snippet.title: Woman Who Shot Coldplay Kisscam Speaks Out
snippet.description: The woman who shot that Coldplay kisscam that caught a pair of executives in a private moment is speaking out to Inside Edition. Grace Springer captured the moment Andy Byron, CEO of billion-dollar A.I. company Astronomer, and Kristin Cabot, the company's head of human resources, were seen shrinking in panic from a cozy clinch at the concert in Boston. Fortune magazine is predicting "severe consequences for the company's culture, reputation, and financial stability."

snippet.title: Mumbo Update 2025
snippet.description:
Today I give you all an update on what's going with me in 2025, 3 years after leaving YouTube. I talk about Hermitcraft Season 10, my plans for Hermitcraft Season 11, retiring from YouTube and my struggles with disordered eating. 

I am not a professional; I would highly recommend seeking professional advice from therapists specialising in disordered eating if this is something youâ€™re deeply struggling with.

My first piece of advice is to look at lifestyle transformation over a macro time scale as opposed to focusing on quick fixes. I would put myself on these unsustainable restrictive diets, tell myself I needed to exercise at an incredible intensity almost daily, and within a week I be would exhausted, unmotivated and inevitably fall off the wagon - I would then beat myself up for â€˜failing againâ€™ and comfort myself by bingeing heavily. 

One thing that really helped me is getting 3-4 incredibly quick recipes that I can cook. Iâ€™m talking less than 5 minutes. Are they the absolute healthiest wholefood gold standard? No. But a perfect gold standard recipe that takes a trip to the shop and 30 minutes to prepare actually means Iâ€™m eating a triple cheese blend pizza hut for dinner as soon as Iâ€™m under any time pressure.

Some examples of these hyper fast meals:

- Microwave burrito bean mix rice, Microwave chill non-carne, Tofu, tenderstem brocolli, some feta cheese. All chucked in a single pan. Over 80g of protein, loads of fibre. 5 minutes max.
- A cold pasta pot (tomato and herb), tofu, feta cheese. All in one pan literally just to heat it, maybe 3 minutes? I will also mix up the pasta pots for pesto/chilli ones for variety.
- Stir fry mix. Some kind of noodle packet with flavouring provided, a stirfry veg mix, tofu. Maybe 5 minutes?
- Falaffels and couscous, maybe some humous and pita breads.

Again, are they perfect? No. But you have to think of the reality. You can write out the perfect plan with macro calories calculated to the second decimal place, a huge veg variety, and 12 hours of exercise mapped to all the different muscle groups, but a plan is just a plan, it doesnâ€™t exist. The real story is how you interact with it, and if you canâ€™t sustain your plan for more than 3 days itâ€™s not really a plan at all. These meals are delicious, easy, satiating, cheap, available from basically any shop, last for days in the fridge, and take less time than ordering takeaways. Having these burden free options mean you are likely to integrate them into a sustainable lifestyle change, as opposed to hunting for absolute perfection.

On that note; a lot of people with disordered eating listen to health and wellness podcasts. I would possibly recommend stopping that, they tend to fear monger and hyperbolise the negative effects of relatively innocuous foods. This again can lead to catastrophizing the tiniest of â€˜imperfectionsâ€™ such as eating an â€˜ultra processed protein barâ€™ or drinking a sugar free soda. I switched out my â€˜healthâ€™ podcasts for ones that focus on hobbies I enjoy, and that was far better.

I got rid of my scale, I havenâ€™t weighed myself in about a year. Your weight fluctuates a lot daily, and those swings I really struggled with. If I was heavily restricting and woke up heavier I would immediately give up. I would also restrict super hard excited by how much I could lose in a day. Getting rid immediately switched my mentality from thinking on a daily timescale to a long term one. I do take â€˜progressâ€™ photos every now again, and my health metrics are tracked by my apple watch, but I donâ€™t really put much effort into any measurements. 

In terms of activity, my lifestyle shift happened over 3 years: I began indoor climbing 1-2 times a week, I then slowly built a friend group around climbing who I love spending time with, my love for indoor climbing then spread to a love for outdoor climbing, which then meant I started training for hiking, which gave me the fitness to pursue alpine climbing. I prioritise these hobbies and do them whenever I get any free time, because I love them and my life is built around them. Instead of going for food/drinking with friends we go climbing. If we all get a free day, we go hiking. If we sync up weeks off we go on a trip to the mountains. I know most people have less flexible schedules than me, and kids etc. massively complicate things, but if you can find a form of exercise that you truly love, be it BJJ, running, roller derby, skateboarding, surfing, yoga etc. and build your social structure around it, things will fall into place. To put it simply, I donâ€™t think of anything I do as â€˜exerciseâ€™ I just view it as fun, in the same way a kid doesnâ€™t view running everywhere and playing tag as a workout!

But as I say - this is all a process. Having spent a full day editing this and hearing myself talk about food the whole time, I ordered a pizza lol

snippet.title: Exclusive: Wife speaks after husband sucked into MRI machine dies, says he was 'snatched' | News 12
snippet.description:
A Nassau County woman is recalling the harrowing experience of her husband being pulled into an MRI machine by the metal chain around his neck. Keith McAllister was critically injured when he was pulled into the machine and later died from his injuries, according to Nassau County police. It happened Wednesday afternoon at Nassau Open MRI in Westbury on Long Island. Adrienne Jones-McAllister says she saw her husband walk toward the table and saw the machine "snatch him."

nl-NL.description:
Een vrouw uit Nassau County herinnert zich de aangrijpende ervaring toen haar man aan de metalen ketting om zijn nek in een MRI-scanner werd getrokken. Keith McAllister raakte ernstig gewond toen hij in de scanner werd getrokken en overleed later aan zijn verwondingen, aldus de politie van Nassau County. Het gebeurde woensdagmiddag in de Nassau Open MRI in Westbury op Long Island. Adrienne Jones-McAllister zegt dat ze haar man naar de tafel zag lopen en zag hoe de scanner hem "greep".

snippet.title: Gyokeres? We need MORE PLAYERS | Mikel Arteta | Arsenal in Asia
snippet.description:
Arsenal manager Mikel Arteta updates progress on the club's pursuit of Viktor Gyokeres and other transfer targets on the first day of their pre-season tour of Singapore.

TIMESTAMPS
0:00 INTRO
0:05 excited about new season after great training with new signings in Spain. Adapting to weather and unable to train this morning
0:45 new signings like 'shaking the tree' and bring new energy - heights need to go to a new level
1:10 players are convinced how good they are and ready to take the next step.
1:58 Zubimendi? a long process and he could have gone elsewhere but he wanted to come to Arsenal and we are all so impressed now we have seen him in training.
2:49 Gyokeres? Can't comment on player who is not part of our group yet
3:10 four signings already - can we expect more players to sign and come to Singapore? Still a long time to go and we are still short on numbers
3:40 Who can get into first team from young players? Whoever knocks down the door - up to them
4:08 Partey charges reaction? club has been clear that legal matters mean I can not comments
4:40 confident club followed right processes? 100 per cent 
4:57 Calafiori expectations for his second season?  his injuries last season were on international duty with Italy and now we want him consistently available.
6:01 changes since you played in Singapore with Arsenal ten years ago? our supporters here are v passionate and we want to connect with them.
7:11 ten years ago I did not expect to be sitting here (as manager) 
7:50 four players in still hopes we can improve the team
8:33 I am pleased with where we are so far in the transfer window and hopeful there will be more very soon
8:52 window has been exciting as seen ambition club has throughout the club

Arsenal manager Mikel Arteta updates progress on the club's pursuit of Viktor Gyokeres and other transfer targets on the first day of their pre-season tour of Singapore.

3:10 four signings already - can we expect more players to sign and come to Singapore? Still a long time to go and we are still short on numbers
3:40 Who can get into first team from young players? Whoever knocks down the door - up to them
4:08 Partey charges reaction? club has been clear that legal matters mean I can not comments
4:40 confident club followed right processes? 100 per cent 
4:57 Calafiori expectations for his second season?  his injuries last season were on international duty with Italy and now we want him consistently available.
6:01 changes since you played in Singapore with Arsenal ten years ago? our supporters here are v passionate and we want to connect with them.
7:11 ten years ago I did not expect to be sitting here (as manager) 
7:50 four players in still hopes we can improve the team
8:33 I am pleased with where we are so far in the transfer window and hopeful there will be more very soon
8:52 window has been exciting as seen ambition club has throughout the club

10:02 Madueke - why so many Chelsea players? They have a lot of great players and we focus on who we want rather than the club they are in. he is having a break aftyer winning the Club World Cup and the players who know him are delighted we have signed him.

snippet.title: We Went To Canada To See The U.S. Product Boycotts â€” And What We Found Was Striking
snippet.description:
In response to U.S. tariffs and President Trump's policies, 71% of Canadian consumers are shifting away from American products, with the "Buy Canada" movement. CNBC traveled to Canada to speak with locals and meet with a grocery store owner to find out the impact of the boycotts. As the U.S. economy is projected to lose up to $90 billion in 2025 due to shifting consumer sentiment. The fallout is global with Mexico and countries in the European Union joining. And it extends to tourism, with Canadian visits to the U.S. down 50%, crippling U.S. border economies.

snippet.title: will.i.am + Taboo - EAST LA (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
will.i.am + Taboo - East LA (Official Music Video)

We are Los Angeles. We are Angelenos. We are Americans. Some of us born here, some of us migrated here. We are a great country and our borders should be protected. You would think that the idea of border control would make residents feel safe - but it's pumped fear into our communities. 

They're going after people that make our city beautiful. People who put food in our supermarkets, take care of other people's kids, work two to three jobs so they can take care of their families. It breaks my heart. 

I wanted to make this video to change the vibe and celebrate the folks that make our cities great. The very same people who are being disregarded, dehumanized, and demoralized. 

Thank you for your contributions. Thank you for your work. We will get through this.

snippet.description:
Watch the brand-new trailer for Tron: Ares and experience it in theaters, filmed for IMAX, October 10.
 
Tron: Ares follows a highly sophisticated Program, Ares, who is sent from the digital world into the real world on a dangerous mission, marking humankindâ€™s first encounter with A.I. beings. The feature film is directed by Joachim RÃ¸nning and stars Jared Leto, Greta Lee, Evan Peters, Hasan Minhaj, Jodie Turner-Smith, Arturo Castro, Cameron Monaghan, with Gillian Anderson, and Jeff Bridges. Sean Bailey, Jeffrey Silver, Justin Springer, Jared Leto, Emma Ludbrook and Steven Lisberger are the producers, with Russell Allen serving as executive producer.

GrammyÂ®-award winning rock band Nine Inch Nails composed the score for â€œTron: Ares,â€ and today, the band dropped "As Alive As You Need Me To Be" â€”the soundtrack albumâ€™s first single and the first official music from the band in five years. Listen to "As Alive As You Need Me To Beâ€ and view the visualizer: https://nineinchnails.lnk.to/AAAYNMTB. The track is featured in the new trailer for â€œTron: Ares.â€
 
â€œTron: Ares (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack),â€ featuring all original music by Nine Inch Nails, will be released on September 19 via Interscope Records. The release marks the first-ever film score by the pioneering band, although bandmates Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross have composed 20 scores under their own names, winning two OscarsÂ®, three Golden GlobesÂ®, a GRAMMYÂ® and an EmmyÂ® in the process.

snippet.title: Past Life #2 - Remember This?
snippet.description:
Past Life is an odd mix of a Social and PvP Minecraft game started by Grian. Players are thrown into a tiny world with almost no rules, except survive as long as possible.

In Past Life, we will be playing through the older versions of Minecraft and updating to a newer one each episode.

3+ Lives = Green Player
2 Lives = Yellow Player
1 Life = Red Player

Red Players are given the goal of killing all the other players in the game. Yellow Players can kill Green Players.

snippet.title: Watch live: SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket launches 24 Starlink satellites to polar orbit from California
snippet.description:
Watch live coverage as SpaceX launches a Falcon 9 rocket carrying 24 of its Starlink V2 Mini satellite into a polar orbit. Liftoff of the Starlink 17-3 mission from pad 4E at Vandenberg Space Force Base is scheduled for Friday, July 18, at 8:52 p.m. PDT / 11:52 p.m. EDT (0352 UTC on Saturday, July 19). The first-stage booster, tail number B1082, making its 14th flight, will land on the drone ship 'Of Course I Still Love You' about eight and a half minutes after launching.

Our live coverage with commentary will begin about 30 minutes before launch.

Videos like this are made possible by the support of our members. Join this channel to get access to perks:

Mortal Kombat 2 is in theaters on October 24.

snippet.title: Reuniting With My Family and Girlfriend After 2 Years
snippet.description:
MY BROTHER IS HOME!! ğŸ˜­âœˆï¸ Emotional Missionary Homecoming After 2 Years

After two years away, Brock is finally HOME!! He spent the last year and a half serving in Boston, Massachusetts, and this vlog captures the unforgettable moments leading up to his return. From packing his (very heavy) bags and saying goodbye to mission friends, to getting paired with a final companionâ€”his journey back was emotional and full of meaning.

id.title: Turun 45 KG, Menangkan $250.000!
id.description:
**Dalam Kenangan Penuh Kasih untuk Coach Tyler Wall**

Dengan kesedihan yang mendalam, kami menyampaikan kabar meninggalnya Pelatih Tyler Wall. Pelatih Wall adalah sosok luar biasa yang kebaikan dan semangatnya yang tulus menyentuh hati semua orang yang mengenalnya. Kehilangannya membuat hati kami sangat berduka.

Menyusul berita tragis ini, kami menghubungi keluarga Pelatih Wall untuk menentukan apakah video ini harus dibagikan. Dengan keanggunan dan kebijaksanaan, mereka menyatakan bahwa Tyler ingin pesannya yang penuh harapan dan kepositifan terus menjangkau orang lain, bahkan saat ia tidak ada.

Kami dengan rendah hati meminta Anda untuk menghormati kenangan Pelatih Wall dan menghargai kebutuhan keluarganya akan privasi selama masa sulit ini.

Warisan kasih sayang dan dorongan Pelatih Tyler Wall akan terus hidup di hati semua orang yang cukup beruntung untuk mengenalnya.

Ein groÃŸes DankeschÃ¶n an alle, die uns von der Reise gelobt haben â€“ Atlanta war fantastisch. Bleibt dran, wir haben den Rest des Sommers noch VIEL mehr Inhalte fÃ¼r euch! ğŸ’¯

localized.title: Stranger Things Season 5 Teaser Trailer BREAKDOWN!
localized.description:
Here is my BREAKDOWN of the official teaser trailer for Stranger Things Season 5! The final season of the hit Netflix show releases in 3 volumes: Vol 1 on November 26, Vol 2 on December 25 and the finale on December 31 of this year. Find out my in-depth thoughts, predictions and theories now...

COMMENT your thoughts on the Stranger Things Season 5 teaser trailer down below! Hit that LIKE button and SUBSCRIBE to help me reach my goal of 150,000 subscribers!

WANT EXTRA STRANGER THINGS CONTENT? JOIN MY PATREON:
https://www.patreon.com/filmstocked

Stranger Things Season 5 stars Millie Bobby Brown as Eleven, Finn Wolfhard as Mike Wheeler, Noah Schnapp as Will Byers, Gaten Matarazzo as Dustin Henderson, Caleb McLaughlin as Lucas Sinclair, Winona Ryder as Joyce Byers, David Harbour as Hopper, Joe Keery as Steve Harrington, Maya Hawke as Robin Buckley, Natalia Dyer as Nancy Wheeler, Charlie Heaton as Jonathan Byers, Sadie Sink as Max Mayfield, Jamie Campbell Bower as Vecna/Henry Creel/001, Cara Buono as Karen Wheeler, Priah Ferguson as Erica Sinclair, Brett Gelman as Murray Bauman and more.
